{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/data-science-in-business-e3c94c76c182", "time": 1683002225.348403, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/data-science-in-business-e3c94c76c182/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Data Science in Business. Business Data Science in a nutshell | by Przemek Chojecki | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Data Science in Business", "description": "Data Science is everywhere. Every single business, if it wants to stay competitive, has to apply Data Science to some extent, in order to understand clients and the market. On the other hand, we\u2019re\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/practical-guide-to-become-a-data-scientist-2483a5f83770", "anchor_text": "Practical guide to Data Science", "paragraph_index": 9}], "all_paragraphs": ["Data Science is everywhere. Every single business, if it wants to stay competitive, has to apply Data Science to some extent, in order to understand clients and the market. On the other hand, we\u2019re lacking so many people in Data Science that it\u2019s the best time to consider a career change. This post is directed at business people who want to learn data science.", "Data science is all about understanding data and that\u2019s crucial in business. It\u2019s mostly done in Python or R (programming languages) with the goal to extract interesting actionable information from business data.", "One of the common problems in real estate is predicting prices and classifying price ranges to evaluate what can be sold and what not. Data Science helps classify properties into different classes and then through regression allows to predict prices based on past transactions.", "On the other hand if you don\u2019t know who are your customers, the best way to learn about it is to use clustering techniques. Data Science allows you to group your customers by similarity: shopping history, demographics, etc. This way you know what you\u2019re selling to whom.", "If you\u2019re shopping on Amazon or watching Netflix then you probably know that they are using powerful recommendation systems to suggest you new products to buy or series to watch. It\u2019s actually possible to build one for your business \u2014 once you cluster your customers and predict prices, you can start building a recommendation engine.", "Finally to understand your data, you need to separate standard/mean from outliers or anomalies. This way you can predict who\u2019s exactly your average customer.", "If you\u2019ve already got all your data crunched and ready to be used, the final stage consists of making it visual so that other team members can understand what you\u2019re doing. Within Python and R you have several tools (like plotly or Dash) which you can use to visualize your data in business. And then of course Excel and Powerpoint!", "If you\u2019ve watched this mini-course then you\u2019re well-prepared to start building a data science strategy for your business.", "It\u2019s the best time to implement some of the tools to grow your venture.", "If you\u2019re looking for more materials on Data Science check Practical guide to Data Science.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "AI & crypto, PhD in mathematics, Forbes 30 under 30, former Oxford fellow."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fe3c94c76c182&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdata-science-in-business-e3c94c76c182&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdata-science-in-business-e3c94c76c182&source=po